In [4]:
### replace 0 instead of Np.nan in our cementatious material
Data1['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data1['Cement(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Cement(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data1['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data1['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data1['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data1['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)'] = Data1['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
In [5]:
### Compute W/B in our data
Binder = Data1['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'] + Data1['Cement(Kg/m3)'] + Data1['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'] + Data1['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'] + Data1['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'] + Data1['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)']
Data1['W/B'] = Data1['Water(Kg/m3)']/Binder

In [20]:
### Bogue method for calculation the percentage of four major compounds
Data1['C3S'] = 4.07*Data1['CaO_Cement'] - 7.6*Data1['SiO2_Cement'] - 6.72*Data1['Al2O3_Cement'] - 1.43*Data1['Fe2O_Cement'] - 2.85*Data1['SO3_Cement']
Data1['C2S'] = 2.87*Data1['SiO2_Cement'] - 0.754*(3*Data1['CaO_Cement']*Data1['SiO2_Cement'])
Data1['C3A'] = 2.65*Data1['Al2O3_Cement'] - 1.69*Data1['Fe2O_Cement']
Data1['C4AF'] = 3.04*Data1['Fe2O_Cement']

import sklearn.datasets as datasets
from sklearn.externals.six import StringIO
from sklearn.tree import export_graphviz
import pylab
import pandas as pd
import pydotplus
import graphviz

from IPython.display import Image
dtree = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=4)
dtree.fit(X_train,y_train)

    out_file = dot_data,

    rounded = True,
    special_characters = True,feature_names = X.columns,rotate =True
)
